text: Followed this dessert stall staff from her former dessert stall where she worked to her own stall in this coffeeshop. Consistent delicious desserts and the chendol is easily the best I’ve had in Sg. A lot of effort goes in to ensure that every dessert tastes good. Strongly recommended.
Like the nasi Dagang there. Fish curry meal is good . The staff is friendly and serve with smile

Good atmosphere here, had the chicken rice and the soup was GREAT, the chicken is slightly less amazing but overall, food was good. In terms of being clean, it’s quite clean, no odd smell anything. So if you want a quick bite you can come here to grab something.

Bought some pastry before & was not so fresh. Heard from friends they experienced it too & noticed the stall is always overstock with food items, thus are not fresh.
Ytd night passed by bought the AKK. This morning opened & found all sticky & mouldy.
Ban this stall now.
Hope the coffeeshop management do something.

Typical neighborhood kopitiam but with decent foods. Like the noodle stall and believe is partnership of Fei Shiong. The ban Mian stall also has nice dumpling. But the economical veg rice stall has a short hair aunty who is very rule, like all eaters own her money. 19 Nov - Dropped two stars from the previous review. Food standard has dropped badly. Ordered the ginger with onion fish rice from the mix rice stall zhi char, I would say this the worst dish I ever had.
